      • bufferUp

        public Connection.Response bufferUp()
        从接口复制的说明: Connection.Response
        Read the body of the response into a local buffer, so that Connection.Response.parse() may be called repeatedly on the same connection response (otherwise, once the response is read, its InputStream will have been drained and may not be re-read). Calling Connection.Response.body() or Connection.Response.bodyAsBytes() has the same effect.
        指定者:
        bufferUp 在接口中 Connection.Response
        返回:
        this response, for chaining

      • bodyStream

        public BufferedInputStream bodyStream()
        从接口复制的说明: Connection.Response
        Get the body of the response as a (buffered) InputStream. You should close the input stream when you're done with it. Other body methods (like bufferUp, body, parse, etc) will not work in conjunction with this method.

        This method is useful for writing large responses to disk, without buffering them completely into memory first.

        指定者:
        bodyStream 在接口中 Connection.Response
        返回:
        the response body input stream
